## Supabase MCP (Cursor Cloud Agents)

Two MCP entries — one per Supabase **project** (not per app). Add each separately in **Settings → Tools & MCP → Cloud** (one server per modal; do not paste both in one box).

| MCP name | Covers | `project_ref` |
|----------|--------|---------------|
| `supabase-greetq` | GreetQ | `lrihhjjxmxixppmrzvva` |
| `supabase-ratelocal` | RateLocal | `otnddwopphhxstteqizw` |
| `supabase-servelocal` | ServeLocal (TRADELOCAL) | `avytxgfkncpacqewnrvz` |

Config shape per entry: `{ "url": "https://mcp.supabase.com/mcp?project_ref=<ref>" }`. Repo copy: `.cursor/mcp.json`. Sign in to Supabase when Cursor prompts. Optional: append `&read_only=true` for safer dev queries.

Verify Supabase works by hitting production APIs — do not assume broken if Vercel UI glitches.

## Cold email outreach (Activepieces → API)

Daily sends are **not** configured in Vercel UI. Activepieces calls:

- GreetQ: `POST https://greetq.com/api/make/outreach/daily` — header `X-GreetQ-Secret: <ACTIVEPIECES_MARKETING_WEBHOOK_SECRET>`
- RateLocal: `POST https://ratelocal.ca/api/make/outreach/daily` — header `X-RateLocal-Secret: <ACTIVEPIECES_MARKETING_WEBHOOK_SECRET>`

Schedule (Pacific, weekdays): GreetQ **11:00**, RateLocal **14:00**.

Batching: **20 × 5 emails** per run (5 per API call) to avoid Vercel 504 timeouts.

Lead import: `tools/greetq-lead-scraper/` and `tools/ratelocal-lead-scraper/` → import API. Empty GreetQ queue = re-import leads, not a token failure.

## Google login errors

`{"message":"Unrecognized client_id"}` = **Google OAuth** misconfig in Supabase → Authentication → Providers → Google (not the service role key).

Redirect URI in Google Cloud must include: `https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback`

